cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the task of panoptic segmentation, which involves both semantic segmentation and instance segmentation. The dataset used is an extension of SemanticKITTI, which provides dense point-wise semantic labels for LiDAR point clouds. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), which deals with image and video analysis. The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) since it deals with LiDAR data, which is commonly used in robotics applications. Machine learning (cs.LG) is also likely since the paper discusses the use of state-of-the-art approaches for segmentation and detection. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) are less likely categories since they are not directly related to the content of the paper.
